Japan's Prime Minister Condemns Anti-Japan Rallies in China
TOKYOâ€”Japan's prime minister on Sunday deplored the escalating anti-Japan rallies in China and emphasized his commitment to continue to assert sovereignty over disputed islets, but he also signaled his desire to retain healthy economic ties with Beijing amid Japan's sharpening economic slowdown.
The remarks from Yoshihiko Noda suggest that while he doesn't intend to reverse the recent nationalization of the islets by his administration, he is growing concerned about potential economic fallout from the territorial dispute....